article.headline: Indiana St. 92, Wagner 86, OT
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Gabe Moore scored a career-high 29 points and had eight assists to lead Indiana State as the Sycamores defeated Wagner 92-86 in overtime. Jay Tunnell added 17 points and 11 rebounds for the Sycamores (6-4). Mark Porter led Wagner (4-8) with 21 points as the Seahawks led the entire first half and hit seven first-half 3-point shots. A 3-pointer by Trent Wurtz gave the Sycamores their first lead with 18:34 remaining, but Indiana State never led by more than four points in the second half. Tunnell's layup with four seconds left sent the game into overtime. The Sycamores outscored the Seahawks 14-8 in overtime. Adam Arnold came off the bench to add 13 points and 10 rebounds for Indiana State. Wagner held a 40-35 rebounding edge, but Indiana State outscored the Seahawks 18-4 in second-chance points.
